ent with soldiers and veterans as flesh-and-blood representatives of the nation. Hymns for the Fallen explores all three elements of film sound—dialogue, sound effects, music—and considers how expressive and formal choices in the soundtrack have turned the serious war film into a patriotic ritual enacted in the commercial space of the cinema.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aFilm soundtracksxHistory and criticism. 0aMotion picture musicxHistory and criticism. 0aWar filmsxHistory and criticism. 7aMUSIC / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aamerican film.  aamerican sniper.  aapocalypse now.  abattle.  ablack hawk down.  acinema studies.  acinema.  acombat films.  acombat training.  acombat.  adialogue.  afilm analysis.  afilm music.  afilm soundtrack.  afilm studies.  afilms about war.  ahollywood.  ahurt locker.  amovies about war.  apatriotic.  asaving private ryan.  asoldiers.  asound effects.  athin red line.  aveterans.  avietnam war films.  avietnam war movies.  avietnam war.  avietnam.  awar films.  awar movies.  awartime.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106675540 cprintz978052028233940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520966543423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520966543/original  a978-3-11-066755-4  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles